UID:e5ebc1dd2b090bb477388e2097ef8cd3@coolpetaluma.org
DESCRIPTION:Cool Petaluma Book Club Our book for April\, Hope in the Dark 
 by Rebecca Solnit\, shows us why we should not give up hope\, even though 
 our future is uncertain. In fact\, we should be committed to it in all its
  unknowability. PLEASE NOTE: There are 5 copies at Copperfield’s\; ask f
 or one at the counter. Let them know you’re with the Cool Petaluma Clima
 te Book Club. Plus\, get 10% off! RSVP Here #block-41ef93226c8a0444c843 {-
 -sqs-block-content-flex: 0\; } Hope in the Dark Solnit’s book is a manif
 esto for hope in place of the despair that engulfs many activists when the
 ir campaigns to make the world a better place or safeguard local values fr
 om globalized corporations do not bear immediate fruit. Solnit advocates f
 or embracing the darkness of an uncertain future and campaigning from the 
 perspective that previously unforeseen changes are always possible. In thi
 s book\, she seeks to safeguard against the cultural amnesia in which peop
 le forget that previously unthinkable events changed history\, such as obt
 aining suffrage for women after millennia of patriarchy. In addition\, she
  emphasizes that no easy cause-and-effect relationship exists between acti
 vism and seeing changes realized. Instead\, the path to change twists and 
 turns\, with many defeats as well as small victories. &nbsp\; [ { "id": "0
 4388466-7135-4ccc-9916-e993de72b63e" } ] Get your copy &amp\; start readin
 g: Petaluma Library GoodReads Copperfield’s Books - Tell them you are wi
 th the Cool Petaluma Book Club for 10% discount! #block-3fc3e09189c2075604
